<h3>Cookies</h3>
<p>Like many websites, our Site and Applications use "cookies" to collect information. A cookie is a small data file that we transfer to your computer or mobile device’s hard disk for record-keeping purposes. We use cookies for two purposes. 
<br/>
First, we utilize persistent cookies to save your login information for future logins to the Site and Applications and also for tracking what are the advertisement showed to you. Persistent cookies that are used for logins are created when you login into our site and it would be deleted when you log out of our application. It would be retained if you dont log out explictly so that you can access our site/applications next time without logging in every time. 
<br/>
The persistent cookiee that we use for advertising is created to track what are the product advertisements served to you so that we can avoid showing the same advertisement multiple times to you or serve the advertisement that is interesting to you. We also use this information for reporting and analyzing the data. This cookie doesnt contain any of your personal information. You can opt out of this cookie tracking from this link (<a href="/opt_out">Opt-Out</a>). 
<br/>
Second, we utilize session ID cookies to enable certain features of the Site and Applications, to better understand how you interact with the Site and Applications and to monitor aggregate usage by Plannto Users and web traffic routing on the Site and Applications. Unlike persistent cookies, session cookies are deleted from your computer when you log off from the Site, Applications and Service and then close your browser. 
<br/>
Third party advertisers on the Site and Applications may also place or read cookies on your browser. You can instruct your browser, by changing its options, to stop accepting cookies or to prompt you before accepting a cookie from the websites you visit. If you do not accept cookies, however, you may not be able to use all portions of the Site and Applications or all functionality of the Service.</p>
